cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with problems related to curves in the plane, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of data structures to efficiently solve these problems suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The problem of finding the center of a set of curves is also related to clustering (cs.SI). Finally, the use of the Frechet distance function suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
